[src:reasonml/pattern-matching] In Haskell and functional programming languages in general, strings are represented as functional lists of characters.
[src:reasonml/pattern-matching] A functional list is defined as an empty list, or an element constructed on an existing list.
[src:reasonml/pattern-matching] The structure for a list with some elements is thus `element:list`.
